  counter-example raw-meta entry whose implementation IS the SSOT row itself (e.g., raw 47 cross-repo-trawl-witness) — finding=registration is self-implementing
  ceiling-type algorithmic
  breakthrough-grade APPROACH
  measurement-axis absorption-coverage-ratio = findings_with_absorption_channel_within_7d / total_actionable_findings over rolling 30d via state/discovery_absorption/registry.jsonl; baseline 2026-04-27 = unknown (registry not bootstrapped); 30d ramp >= 0.70; 90d >= 0.95
  measurement-axis median-absorption-latency-days from finding-emit to implementation-commit; 30d target <= 7d (median); 90d target <= 3d
  witness state/discovery_absorption/registry.jsonl
  classifier-version discovery_absorption_lint.v1
  falsifier 30d post: absorption-coverage-ratio < 0.50 = mandate too strict OR finding scope over-broad = retire OR scope reduction (Tier-A actionable only)
  falsifier 3+ legitimate findings cannot map to any of the 5 realization-channels (e.g., external dependency not yet released, pure measurement that has no implementation surface) = 6th channel needed OR retire
  falsifier median absorption latency > 14d = governance bottleneck, optimize OR retire
  falsifier false-absorption: registry pointer claims absorption but pointed artifact (commit/file/atlas/blocker) actually unchanged or absent = trust broken, classifier-version bump required, immediate fix
  falsifier 1+ actionable finding ABSORBED via channel not in declared list (escape hatch usage) = list incomplete, extend OR retire
  measurement-threshold absorption-coverage-ratio>=0.70-at-30d absorption-coverage-ratio>=0.95-at-90d median-absorption-latency-days<=7-at-30d median-absorption-latency-days<=3-at-90d
