own 5 new "nexus-local: heredoc ARG_MAX content-size guard for nexus/tool MED-risk files (anima own 7 cross-repo mirror — raw 144 nexus scope)"
  slug nexus-heredoc-arg-max-guard
  enforce advisory
  base raw 9 hexa-only + raw 144 exec-cmd-length-guard (universal)
  since 2026-04-28 (anima own 7 cross-repo mirror per raw 47)
  scope nexus git-tracked tool/*.hexa with heredoc-style `cat > <path> <<EOF` pattern inside exec(...)
  rule nexus/tool/*.hexa heredoc cmd-line dynamic-content writes ≥ 4 KiB MUST migrate to native write_file() builtin. Darwin ARG_MAX 1,044,361 bytes empirical cliff (verdict adc2e734 2026-04-28) below which transfer is byte-perfect; above which pclose=32512 hard fail (E2BIG). 'silent' aspect = caller-side `let _r = exec(cmd)` discarding rc — raw 12 silent-error-ban violation when cmd contains user/dataflow content.
  scope MED-risk nexus heredoc sites identified by static survey 2026-04-28:
  note tool/discovery_infra.hexa, tool/consensus_loop.hexa, tool/convergence_update.hexa (data ledger writes — drift potential)
  note tool/dse_delta.hexa, tool/date_n_guard_lint.hexa, tool/l3_guard.hexa, tool/lint_annot.hexa (proposal/cert text emit)
  note tool/psi_calibration_cache.hexa, tool/psi_calibrate_emit.hexa, tool/pass_gate_an11.hexa, tool/psi_calibration_drift.hexa (psi calibration manifests)
  note tool/signal_meta_dead_revival.hexa + 4 sister meta tools (signal_meta_compound_split / retroactive_tag / auto_spec_evolution / self_audit)
  enforcement nexus tool/*.hexa heredoc dynamic-content > 4 KiB sites SHOULD migrate to write_file() within 2026-Q2. CI gate via tool/heredoc_arg_max_lint (hive canonical) cross-repo invocable.
  exception small fixed-content (< 4 KiB) heredoc grandfathered for readability — annotation `// own 5: small-fixed-content` recommended at site.
  bans new nexus tool/*.hexa adding heredoc + dynamic-content > 4 KiB without write_file() migration
  bans assuming 64-128KB threshold without per-OS measurement (raw 91 honest C3 — measure don't guess)
  why nexus tool surface = drill cycle dispatch + atlas absorb sweepers + psi calibration emit + audit ledger appenders. Many tools emit dynamic-size proposal text / cert manifests / ledger rows. Anima own 7 (Bug 1 verdict adc2e734 anima-scope) sister-mirror: nexus has substantively similar exposure surface (16 heredoc tool sites vs anima 4), warranting the same project-local guard. Cross-repo trail per raw 47 — anima registered 2026-04-28, nexus mirror registered same day.
  proof state/format_witness/2026-04-28_own789_cross_repo_mirror.jsonl (cross-repo trawl witness from anima)
  proof anima own 7 entry registered 2026-04-28 with verdict adc2e734 Darwin 1,044,361 bytes measured cliff
  proof Bug 1 verdict agent adc2e734f2badf624 — Darwin ARG_MAX empirical measurement
  severity warn
  cross-repo-trawl-witness anima/state/format_witness/2026-04-28_own789_cross_repo_mirror.jsonl
  strategy-source anima own 7 (heredoc-arg-max-guard 2026-04-28 Bug 1 verdict)
  note 2026-04-28 anima own 7 cross-repo mirror per raw 47. monotonic-invariant compliant — base raw cite (raw 9 + raw 144) + scope narrowing only (anima → nexus tool/*.hexa), no new universal expansion.
  note Linux MAX_ARG_STRLEN=128 KiB per-arg cliff lower than Darwin — cross-OS operation should apply stricter limit.
  follow-up nexus MED-risk tool/*.hexa migration to write_file() for heredoc dynamic-content > 4 KiB
  follow-up CI gate tool/heredoc_arg_max_lint.hexa (hive canonical) cross-repo invocation hook

